## 📋 Complete Technology Inventory

### 1. AI / Computer Vision Layer

| Technology | Purpose | How You Used It |
|:---|:---|:---|
| **Python 3.10+** | Core language | AI engine runtime |
| **YOLOv8 (Ultralytics)** | Object detection + Pose estimation | Real-time person detection and fall detection using `yolov8n.pt` and `yolov8n-pose.pt` models |
| **OpenCV (cv2)** | Video capture & frame processing | Webcam capture, frame annotation, JPEG encoding, image manipulation |
| **NumPy** | Numerical computation | Array operations for keypoint analysis, aspect-ratio calculations |
| **Requests + urllib3** | HTTP client with retry logic | Session-pooled, retry-aware communication with dashboard API |
| **python-dotenv** | Environment variable management | Loading API keys and configuration |
| **ThreadPoolExecutor** | Bounded concurrency | Max 4 threads for async frame + alert sending (avoids thread flooding) |
| **ByteTracker (YOLO built-in)** | Multi-object tracking | Per-person identity tracking across frames |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Key Innovation**: Custom **finite state machine** per tracked person:
> `STANDING → SITTING → FALLING → FALLEN → EMERGENCY`
> Uses dual-method fall detection: **bbox aspect-ratio heuristic** + **pose keypoint analysis**, with temporal filtering (consecutive frame confirmation) to eliminate false positives.

---

### 2. Backend Layer (Node.js)

| Technology | Purpose | How You Used It |
|:---|:---|:---|
| **Node.js 18** | Server runtime | Backend for both SafeSight and MedFlow |
| **Express.js v5** | Web framework | RESTful API routes, middleware pipeline, static file serving |
| **Socket.io v4** | WebSocket real-time communication | Bi-directional events: live video feed, alerts, vitals streaming, patient subscriptions |
| **MongoDB (Mongoose v9)** | NoSQL database | 10+ schemas: Users, Alerts, Patients, Vitals, LabReports, AuditLogs, ApiKeys, Config |
| **JWT (jsonwebtoken)** | Authentication | Stateless token-based auth with 8-hour expiry |
| **bcrypt / bcryptjs** | Password hashing | 12-round salt hashing for user passwords |
| **Helmet.js** | HTTP security headers | Content Security Policy, XSS protection, clickjacking prevention |
| **express-rate-limit** | Rate limiting | Login endpoint: 10 attempts/15min; API: 200 req/min |
| **Morgan** | HTTP request logging | Dev-mode access logging |
| **CORS** | Cross-origin resource sharing | Allowing cross-origin requests from frontend modules |
| **UUID (v4)** | Unique identifier generation | API key generation for edge node authentication |
| **Multer + GridFS** | File upload handling | Lab report file uploads stored in MongoDB GridFS |
| **Nodemailer** | Email service | SMTP-based critical alert email notifications with HTML templates |

---

### 3. Frontend Layer — SafeSight Dashboard (Vanilla JS)

| Technology | Purpose | How You Used It |
|:---|:---|:---|
| **Vanilla JavaScript (ES6+)** | UI logic | ~75K lines of hand-written JS — no framework overhead |
| **Three.js** | 3D WebGL rendering | Wireframe CCTV camera model, particle systems, grid helpers |
| **HTML5 Canvas API** | 2D data visualization | Custom threat charts, pie/donut charts, heatmaps, weekly bar charts, live camera feed simulations |
| **Socket.io Client** | Real-time data | Live alert feed, video frame streaming, system status indicators |
| **CSS3** | Styling | Dark-mode glassmorphism theme, 57K+ lines of custom CSS, scan-line effects, gradient animations |
| **IntersectionObserver** | Scroll-triggered animations | Lazy-load animations, performance-optimized Three.js rendering |
| **RequestAnimationFrame** | Smooth animations | Particle networks, counter animations, camera feed rendering |

