### 4. Frontend Layer — MedFlow Module (React)

| Technology | Purpose | How You Used It |
|:---|:---|:---|
| **React 18** | UI framework | Component-based healthcare dashboard |
| **TypeScript** | Type safety | Full type definitions for all interfaces and API contracts |
| **Vite** | Build tool | Fast HMR dev server, optimized production builds |
| **React Router v6** | Client-side routing | Protected routes with auth guards |
| **Zustand** | State management | Global store for auth, patients, vitals, alerts, and UI state |
| **Three.js + React Three Fiber** | 3D rendering in React | Interactive 3D body model with alert zone spheres |
| **@react-three/drei** | Three.js React helpers | Pre-built 3D components and camera controls |
| **GSAP** | Premium animations | Page entrance animations, login transitions |
| **Framer Motion** | React animations | Component-level transitions and micro-interactions |
| **MediaPipe Pose** | Browser-side AI | Fall detection, distress posture, eye closure — **runs entirely in-browser, zero video transmitted** |
| **Recharts** | Data charts | Vitals sparkline charts and historical data visualization |
| **Axios** | HTTP client | API communication with interceptors |
| **Lucide React** | Icons | Consistent icon system across UI |
| **Tailwind CSS v3** | Utility-first CSS | Responsive layout with custom design tokens |
| **Socket.io Client** | Real-time data | Patient vital subscriptions, nurse alert broadcasts |

---

### 5. Infrastructure & DevOps

| Technology | Purpose | How You Used It |
|:---|:---|:---|
| **Docker** | Containerization | Multi-stage Dockerfiles for both Python and Node.js services |
| **Docker Compose** | Multi-container orchestration | 5 services: web-dashboard, mongodb, medflow-mongo, medflow-server, medflow-client |
| **GitHub Actions** | CI/CD pipeline | 4-job pipeline: Lint Backend → Lint AI → Docker Build → API Smoke Test |
| **Nginx** | Reverse proxy / static server | Production serving of React SPA in MedFlow client container |
| **MongoDB volumes** | Data persistence | Named Docker volumes for database and uploads |
| **Health checks** | Container reliability | HTTP and `mongosh` health checks with retry logic |
| **Flake8** | Python linting | Automated code quality checks in CI |

---

### 6. Security Implementation

| Mechanism | Technology | Detail |
|:---|:---|:---|
| **User Authentication** | JWT + bcrypt | Token-based sessions, salted password hashing |
| **Machine Authentication** | X-API-Key (UUID) | AI edge nodes authenticate via UUID API keys |
| **Rate Limiting** | express-rate-limit | Brute-force protection on login endpoints |
| **HTTP Security** | Helmet.js | CSP, XSS protection, frame guard headers |
| **Audit Logging** | MongoDB | Every login, API access, camera toggle, and incident review is logged |
| **Tiered Access Control** | Custom middleware | Core / Pro / Elite subscription tiers with role-based guards |

